{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EwLYvEAKqbgUX2p1wYJww8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is in order. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The `report-user` credentials existed only in the `user-provided-file-realm` secret, which was never mounted into the ES pods. The `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret (mounted as the live file realm) only contained `ops-user`.\n\n**Fix (3 steps):**\n\n1. **Merged secrets** — appended `report-user`'s bcrypt hash and `viewer:report-user` role mapping into `es-file-realm-aggregate`, so both users live in one source of truth.\n\n2. **Mounted the secret into the StatefulSet** — patched the `es-cluster` StatefulSet to mount `es-file-realm-aggregate` at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users` and `.../users_roles`. Elasticsearch 8's file realm reads these paths by default — no `elasticsearch.yml` changes needed.\n\n3. **Seeded the `app-data` index** — the rolling restart lost the previously seeded index data; re-created it so `report-user` (with the built-in `viewer` role) can read the document count.\n\n**Verification:**\n- `ops-user` → cluster health `green` ✓\n- `report-user` → `app-data/_count` returns `{\"count\":1}` ✓\n- All 3 ES nodes running, cluster green ✓"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":285,"cache_read_input_tokens":50500,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":285},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17d535c7-bc5a-47f3-bf1c-d18b808e7c60","uuid":"1be191c8-3be7-45cf-ab89-bd86de6ae43e","request_id":"req_011CcQAj5rU3dGgg6m3fPn1V"}
